[[Gardener]]s who have achieved fame through their pioneering innovations, writing or, more often, their [[television]] personas, may be classed as '''celebrity gardeners'''.
The writing of [[Helena Rutherfurd Ely]], [[C. Z. Guest]] and [[Esther Deans]] brought them enough fame for them to be considered celebrity gardeners.
In England, the [[Royal Horticultural Society]] has described both [[Alan Titchmarsh]] and [[Monty Don]] as celebrity gardeners.<ref>[http://www.rhs.org.uk/whatson/events/documents/debatetherapy.pdf#search=%22RHS%20celebrity%20gardener%20alan%22].</ref><ref>[http://www.rhs.org.uk/thegarden/pubs/garden0903/compass0903.pdf#search=%22%22celebrity%20gardener%22%20monty%22].</ref>
