{{notability|date=September 2018}}

'''Norman Saul Matloff''' (born December 16, 1948) is an American professor of [[computer science]] at the [[University of California, Davis]].  He received his Doctor of Philosophy degree in 1975 from the [[mathematics]] department at the [[University of California, Los Angeles]] under the supervision of [[Thomas M. Liggett]].

Matloff is also prominent for certain political writings. He views the increased use of [[H-1B visa]]s in the high technology field as an unnecessary practice that harms the prospects of Americans in the field, and was featured in national American media on this topic.{{fact|date=September 2018}}

